# Apply Google-style Python docstrings.

Add docstrings to public functions, API handlers, service-layer functions, factory functions, lifecycle functions, and architecture-boundary functions.

Do not add docstrings to trivial private helpers unless the behavior is non-obvious.

Do not add comments that merely restate the code. Comments should explain intent, invariants, side effects, or architecture boundaries.

Use Args, Returns, and Raises sections only when applicable.